snippet.textDisplay:
I have a love hate relationship with this type of game.
Yes I've learned his patterns, yes I understand what I'm suppposd to be doing, but all it takes is one extra roll and or dodging one extra strike and im out of stamina - I take one extra hit and im dead.
I've beaten him once before but never got that supposed rush of satisfaction people claim these titles are supposed to give - it was a relief to not have to keep fighting him again, but not enough to keep playing because I knew more of this was all the game held in its future. There are better ways to tell a story, and though the setting is interesting: I just don't get why people enjoy these games.
For all the effort that goes into playinh a Souls game, I can literally be off doing anything else and it feels like a better use if my time. It just feels like masochism and bragging rights.

If he tries to jump or grab you, he will be stunned for a hot second, allowing you to get some easy hits in.

For the second phase, just start slashing and pray.

Second form is nerve wracking first time. You're bound to go "WTF IS THAT??!" and then you're dead. Cuz, you were looking at the black shiny mass above, not his gigantic left arm below.
This one, you keep to his right. (Like in the video)

2022!! Damn it! Thank you for this!!
